1
00:01:17,830 --> 00:01:19,220
Pull yourself together.

2
00:01:21,660 --> 00:01:23,440
I said, pull yourself together!

3
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:03,550
[ 1 year later ]

4
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:47,660
Let's eat.

5
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,130
Eat slowly.

6
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,730
[ Screenwriter, Lee Hee Su ]

7
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,710
These cucumber pickles are really delicious!

8
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,200
Yi Na had really liked eating these!

9
00:05:52,330 --> 00:05:53,640
No more of it?

10
00:06:09,770 --> 00:06:11,200
Why is it so quiet?

11
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,000
I guess he has been hungry all this time.

12
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:16,800
He ate a whole bowl of rice.

13
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:18,280
Goodness.

14
00:06:19,370 --> 00:06:22,880
When he had difficulty in bowel and diarrhea,
he eat three meals a day.

15
00:06:59,910 --> 00:07:01,260
It's strange.

16
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:02,660
It suddenly got quiet.

17
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:20,350
[ My Wife's Bed ]

18
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:10,840
Tell me once again.

19
00:10:11,970 --> 00:10:14,820
I want to stay here for the meantime.

20
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,460
Why?

21
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:48,800
What's wrong?

22
00:10:50,310 --> 00:10:51,530
Father-in-law, the thing is...

23
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:53,770
We're going on the same way,
so can I ride in too?

24
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:56,220
I mean, I...

25
00:10:56,570 --> 00:10:59,060
I haven't had enough sleep these days.

26
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:01,260
And from what I see, we're just...

27
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:03,510
...going on the same way to our work places.

28
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:05,040
If I can get in your car...

29
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:05,550
Get in.

30
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:06,930
Yes. Thanks.

31
00:11:13,460 --> 00:11:15,170
Dad, shall I drive?

32
00:11:15,170 --> 00:11:16,060
Fasten your seat belt.

33
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:50,350
I want to make a change of address.

34
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,000
Yes.

35
00:11:55,640 --> 00:12:00,200
Heukseok-dong, Dongjak-gu, Seoul City.

36
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:14,110
Yes, thank you.

37
00:12:16,710 --> 00:12:17,750
Are you moving out?

38
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:19,370
I have already moved.

39
00:12:19,370 --> 00:12:20,600
Where?

40
00:12:36,370 --> 00:12:37,600
At my late wife's family.

41
00:12:52,420 --> 00:12:54,220
Mother-in-law, I'm back.

42
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:54,860
Hey, Ji Hyeon...

43
00:12:54,860 --> 00:12:57,200
Why are you here? What's going on?

44
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,350
Mom.

45
00:13:04,060 --> 00:13:05,600
Why are you here, Dad?

46
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,480
That's what I wanted to ask too, you punk.

47
00:13:15,770 --> 00:13:16,930
It's just that...

48
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:27,570
And then?

49
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,130
That's why...

50
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:33,660
I'm staying at Yi Na's room.

51
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:35,260
I mean, not together with her.

52
00:13:35,970 --> 00:13:40,000
Dad, I can't sleep if I'm alone.

53
00:13:40,530 --> 00:13:42,860
I'm scared of being alone.

54
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:43,770
Please wait a minute.

55
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:45,280
There's a call.

56
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,130
I mean...

57
00:13:50,860 --> 00:13:53,750
This is where Yi Na had grown up.

58
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:56,770
I feel liberty. Her father and mother are here too.

59
00:13:56,770 --> 00:13:57,910
If I'm together with them...

60
00:13:57,910 --> 00:13:59,330
I mean, not together.

61
00:13:59,330 --> 00:14:01,020
Can you speak properly!?

62
00:14:01,020 --> 00:14:02,170
You startled me!

63
00:14:02,170 --> 00:14:03,510
Why are you so ignorant?

64
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:05,020
Don't you know what you're doing?

65
00:14:07,510 --> 00:14:10,600
Is there a need to explain
why you shouldn't be here?

66
00:14:10,930 --> 00:14:12,480
You see, in-laws.

67
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,930
- For a moment...
- I'm really sorry.

68
00:14:15,310 --> 00:14:17,910
I didn't raised him well.

69
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:21,040
- It's so noisy!
- That startled me!

70
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:25,000
Well, let me take this call first.

71
00:14:27,350 --> 00:14:29,530
Dad, it's you who's the noisiest here!

72
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:33,640
Hello?

73
00:14:34,510 --> 00:14:36,000
Yes, that's me.

74
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:40,570
Yes, I have already moved.

75
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:45,280
What? A courier?

76
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:48,460
What?

77
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:55,370
Congratulations!

78
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:59,080
Congratulations!

79
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:01,460
Congratulations!

80
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:06,260
Congratulations on your 2nd wedding anniversary!

81
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:06,080
Congratulations!

82
00:15:07,510 --> 00:15:08,930
Congratulations!

83
00:15:08,930 --> 00:15:10,860
Let's scream and shout! Yeah!

84
00:15:15,510 --> 00:15:16,600
Yes...

85
00:15:27,350 --> 00:15:29,280
Yi Na!

86
00:15:37,660 --> 00:15:38,730
Hey.

87
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:41,240
It seems we have to do the Plan B.

88
00:15:53,350 --> 00:15:54,600
Thanks.

89
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:22,040
Just leave him alone.

90
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,350
Why are you like this!?

91
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:25,660
He has a reason for him to do that.

92
00:16:27,860 --> 00:16:28,930
That's not it.

93
00:16:29,570 --> 00:16:32,480
You know, I received a gift today.

94
00:16:35,310 --> 00:16:36,930
Shim Jung Woo...

95
00:16:37,970 --> 00:16:39,220
...and Lee Yi Na's...

96
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:42,330
...2nd wedding anniversary congratulatory greetings.

97
00:16:47,130 --> 00:16:49,530
They said it's our wedding anniversary.

98
00:16:54,130 --> 00:16:55,620
But that was...

99
00:16:57,310 --> 00:16:58,950
...Yi Na's death anniversary.

100
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:06,930
Will I get sad or be happy for it?

101
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:08,370
Huh?

102
00:17:10,620 --> 00:17:12,770
Will I get sad or be happy for it?

103
00:17:13,570 --> 00:17:15,640
Does anyone knows? Try to answer it.

104
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:18,530
Answer me! Nobody knows, huh!?

105
00:17:27,530 --> 00:17:29,370
Yi Na...

106
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:32,820
Yi Na!

107
00:17:33,710 --> 00:17:35,770
Yi Na...!

108
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,330
Hurry up.

109
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:40,220
Ouch!

110
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:46,880
Aren't you drunk at all?

111
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,570
I've drank a lot.

112
00:17:48,570 --> 00:17:50,680
This is for the harmony of the two families.

113
00:17:51,060 --> 00:17:52,550
Do you want to tie him up?

114
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:55,400
He won't even know that
we sold him just to make him drunk.

115
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:57,460
Okay. Then, be careful along the way.

116
00:17:57,460 --> 00:17:58,150
- Okay.
- I'll contact you later.

117
00:17:58,150 --> 00:17:59,310
Okay, we're going. Thanks.

118
00:17:59,310 --> 00:18:00,150
Call me later.

119
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:05,930
Yi Na.

120
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:10,550
Let me take care of him by myself.

121
00:18:29,060 --> 00:18:29,930
How about Jung Woo?

122
00:18:29,930 --> 00:18:30,970
He's in the car.

123
00:18:36,710 --> 00:18:38,620
Why am I here?

124
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:43,170
What's that?

125
00:18:43,510 --> 00:18:45,040
What are they doing there?

126
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:46,440
Hurry up and take him!

127
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,000
Yes.

128
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,930
Honey, how 'bout Jung Woo's luggage?

129
00:18:51,950 --> 00:18:53,440
Goodness.

130
00:18:58,060 --> 00:18:59,600
Hey, get out from there.

131
00:19:34,530 --> 00:19:37,060
It's been a long time.
Want to have a drink with me?

132
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:38,310
Okay.

133
00:19:52,020 --> 00:19:53,240
Why is this already empty?

134
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,370
I bought it for the two of us.

135
00:19:56,150 --> 00:19:58,620
Yi Na!

136
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:04,280
I need to go to Yi Na!

137
00:20:04,420 --> 00:20:05,550
Get off, you punk!

138
00:20:05,550 --> 00:20:08,000
I must have to go to her house!

139
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,800
If you're already sober,
know that this is not your home.

140
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:12,550
Let's put his hands away!

141
00:20:12,550 --> 00:20:15,310
Let go of me!

142
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:17,310
- Let go of that!
- Let go of me!

143
00:20:17,310 --> 00:20:18,640
Jung Woo...

144
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:20,970
Just stop this and go home.

145
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:24,600
Honey.

146
00:20:25,510 --> 00:20:27,260
Not there!

147
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,060
Let go of me!

148
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:38,130
Jung Woo!

149
00:20:38,130 --> 00:20:39,200
Jung Woo!

150
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:45,730
I want to go back to Yi Na...!

151
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,680
It's so noisy!

152
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:53,240
Who's that jerk!?

153
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,260
Honey, they had a quarrel.
Let's just go back!

154
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,110
Just go inside!

155
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:00,080
Let go of me!

156
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:08,950
Bring your car key.

157
00:21:10,350 --> 00:21:11,260
Why?

158
00:22:28,860 --> 00:22:30,350
We're really sorry.

159
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,440
Jung Woo.

160
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:03,770
Shim Jung Woo.

161
00:23:18,660 --> 00:23:21,460
Why? Why? Why? What's wrong?

162
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:24,480
The meal is already on the table.
No need to bother her room.

163
00:23:28,910 --> 00:23:31,970
Where did you learn that?
You were not polite to the elders.

164
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:39,930
If you're not just my son,
I should have killed you already!

165
00:23:40,910 --> 00:23:41,840
Come out.

166
00:23:43,330 --> 00:23:44,570
You see, dad.

167
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:49,130
Please just close the door.

168
00:24:20,370 --> 00:24:22,550
How could a man like you cried
as you don't want to move?

169
00:24:23,370 --> 00:24:25,420
How could you say that towards me?

170
00:24:25,420 --> 00:24:27,680
Your tears could overflow the Han River.

171
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,640
Yesterday, I watched it on a cable channel.

172
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:34,570
The amount of tears that people
can shed in their lifetime...

173
00:24:34,570 --> 00:24:36,770
...is about 70 liters.

174
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,330
So what?

175
00:24:38,710 --> 00:24:40,510
Though it doesn't goes the same for anyone,

176
00:24:40,510 --> 00:24:42,170
if it's 70 liters,

177
00:24:42,170 --> 00:24:44,060
I guess it's just about this much.

178
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:46,570
So how could you say that
it'll overflow the Han River?

179
00:24:46,570 --> 00:24:49,550
I don't even know how much toilet paper
you've used after taking out your shit.

180
00:24:49,550 --> 00:24:50,680
I heard about that too.

181
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:54,170
The length of toilet paper used in
a person's lifetime is about 4,200 meters...

182
00:24:54,170 --> 00:24:54,750
Ouch!

183
00:24:55,970 --> 00:24:56,570
That hurts!

184
00:24:59,370 --> 00:24:59,930
Dad...

185
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:05,040
I think my head's bleeding.

186
00:25:14,260 --> 00:25:15,400
Please bill these.

187
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:21,170
It's 32,500 won.

188
00:25:21,570 --> 00:25:22,440
I see.

189
00:25:25,660 --> 00:25:26,880
Who's paying it?

190
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:32,440
It costs 32,500 won.

191
00:25:41,660 --> 00:25:43,020
Please use this.

192
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:43,820
Yes.

193
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:48,040
Thank you.

194
00:25:51,150 --> 00:25:52,710
It's really delicious.

195
00:25:52,930 --> 00:25:55,820
It's just one person, but the expenses have tripled.

196
00:25:56,910 --> 00:25:58,370
I can eat as much as I can.

197
00:25:58,370 --> 00:26:00,000
It's been already a long time.

198
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:02,000
Shouldn't you live for a new life?

199
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:04,420
I can't do that. I have to pay for rent then.

200
00:26:04,420 --> 00:26:06,620
Recently, the real estate market is not good.

201
00:26:06,620 --> 00:26:07,350
What?

202
00:26:07,350 --> 00:26:08,600
Why? What's wrong?

203
00:26:13,730 --> 00:26:14,730
It's nothing.

204
00:26:15,550 --> 00:26:16,800
Hey!

205
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:18,510
Why? What's wrong!?

206
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:19,440
Come back here!

207
00:26:23,020 --> 00:26:23,820
Tell me.

208
00:26:25,110 --> 00:26:26,130
About what?

209
00:26:26,130 --> 00:26:29,220
Why you still want to live there
even Yi Na is already gone?

210
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:35,710
Before I beat you up, just tell me.

211
00:26:36,550 --> 00:26:38,110
You won't really beat me, right?

212
00:26:38,110 --> 00:26:38,970
Right.

213
00:26:48,020 --> 00:26:48,910
You know, dad.

214
00:26:48,910 --> 00:26:49,510
Yes.

215
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:53,280
I do suffer from insomnia.

216
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:55,860
That's the true reason.

217
00:26:58,200 --> 00:26:59,150
Okay.

218
00:27:05,530 --> 00:27:07,510
Whether I get out and live alone,

219
00:27:07,510 --> 00:27:09,640
or go back to my parent's house,

220
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:13,130
they will probably just ask me to get married again.

221
00:27:16,150 --> 00:27:18,970
As what you know, I'm the eldest in the family.

222
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:21,110
I was married and there will be nothing left for them,

223
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:23,880
so they have became conservative too.

224
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:27,420
They still have special attachment from my marriage.

225
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:31,910
Pardon me. I don't really want to say this.

226
00:27:31,910 --> 00:27:32,930
Of course.

227
00:27:35,060 --> 00:27:36,080
You have to get married again.

228
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:38,080
You are already 29 years old now.

229
00:27:38,570 --> 00:27:39,330
What?

230
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:42,110
You mean, I have to get married again?

231
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,130
I don't want to.

232
00:27:43,130 --> 00:27:43,800
What!?

233
00:27:44,020 --> 00:27:46,750
I mean, why are you flaring up?

234
00:27:46,750 --> 00:27:47,550
What are you?!

235
00:27:47,550 --> 00:27:49,730
Why won't you get married again?! Huh?

236
00:27:50,170 --> 00:27:52,260
Is that what you should say at this moment!?

237
00:27:52,260 --> 00:27:53,220
This stupid punk!

238
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:56,480
Of course, I can just call you uncle! Uncle!

239
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,150
Damn you!

240
00:27:58,640 --> 00:28:01,170
Let's forget that. Tell me honestly.

241
00:28:01,170 --> 00:28:03,620
What on earth is the reason
that you went back on our home?

242
00:28:03,620 --> 00:28:04,770
"Our home"?

243
00:28:05,910 --> 00:28:07,930
You're not even a conglomerate
family and it benefits me...

244
00:28:07,930 --> 00:28:08,770
- Damn you!
- You startled me!

245
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:10,330
Damn you!

246
00:28:10,330 --> 00:28:11,660
- Goodness!
- Dad!

247
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:13,770
I mean, dad. What's wrong with you?

248
00:28:23,460 --> 00:28:24,680
You called him Uncle?

249
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:27,130
Anyways, we can just eat enough.

250
00:28:27,130 --> 00:28:28,550
We'll be already full.

251
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,460
My senior.

252
00:28:33,420 --> 00:28:34,620
Who are you?

253
00:28:35,040 --> 00:28:37,550
I'm Chae Ri. Han Chae Ri.

254
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,150
I'm Han Chae Ri.

255
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:43,400
Ah. That Chae Ri...

256
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:45,150
Yes. So you really remembered me.

257
00:28:45,150 --> 00:28:46,840
Right. Yes, Chae Ri.

258
00:28:46,840 --> 00:28:48,150
Please have a lunch with me.

259
00:28:48,150 --> 00:28:49,130
Lunch?

260
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:51,130
I'm going to with my colleagues...

261
00:28:51,130 --> 00:28:52,600
Where did they go?

262
00:28:54,330 --> 00:28:55,150
Hey.

263
00:28:59,350 --> 00:29:00,170
Oh, hey.

264
00:29:00,170 --> 00:29:02,240
Oh, no. There's no need.

265
00:29:06,730 --> 00:29:08,150
Chae Ri, what's up?

266
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:11,000
I'm just asking you to eat with me.

267
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:11,770
Right.

268
00:29:12,110 --> 00:29:13,130
So why?

269
00:29:14,460 --> 00:29:15,820
You don't want to eat?

270
00:29:15,820 --> 00:29:16,910
That's not what I mean.

271
00:29:18,060 --> 00:29:19,200
Just eat.

272
00:29:19,660 --> 00:29:20,770
Let's just eat.

273
00:29:39,330 --> 00:29:40,550
You know, I...

274
00:29:42,020 --> 00:29:43,800
I have really liked you...

275
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:49,930
Sorry.

276
00:29:49,930 --> 00:29:51,170
I'm really sorry.

277
00:29:54,420 --> 00:29:55,570
What did you say?

278
00:29:55,570 --> 00:29:56,600
That is...

279
00:29:57,530 --> 00:29:59,860
I've already told you from the start.

280
00:30:00,420 --> 00:30:02,710
Back when you were my tutor,

281
00:30:02,710 --> 00:30:04,710
I confessed to you that you are my first love.

282
